    <string name="onboarding_get_started">Get Started</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page0_desc">Start by downloading a local AI model in the Settings to enable on-device image analysis.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page1_desc">Use the buttons at the top of the Settings screen to revisit this tutorial, toggle dark or light mode, activate the screen saver to keep your phone awake during analysis, or switch the interface language.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page2_desc">Select your preferred language for the AI to output its analysis results.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page3_desc">Choose how detailed you want the AI to describe your images, from brief to comprehensive, or set a custom prompt.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page4_desc">Add folders from your device to be analyzed automatically. Skarmetoo will sort and index the items inside.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page5_desc">Activate the screen saver to keep your phone awake while the AI analyzes your images in the background.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page6_title">Share Output</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page6_desc">You can share the AI-generated text and the image directly from the detail screen using the share button.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page7_title">Search Images</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page7_desc">Looking for something specific? Use the search bar to find images based on what the AI discovered in them.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page8_title">Filter Pills</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page8_desc">Quickly view images containing specific subjects like people, pets, or food by tapping the suggested filter pills.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page9_title">Reanalyze</string>
    <string name="onboarding_page9_desc">If you want the AI to analyze an image again, simply double-click its status button in the gallery or the detail screen.</string>
